text: My teacher played a video today Today my teacher decided to play a video titled  YOU ARE NOT DEPRESSED  STOP IT  while on the topic of depression and suicide  I ve seen this video multiple times and I do understand the meaning and symbolism behind it  I just feel like it could have been worded better  As someone who has been diagnosed with clinical depression for   years and has to take medication for it  it is not something that can just come and go as easily as he makes it seem  Depression is not a cloud that passes over you  depression is like a wave that crashes into you and tries its hardest to pull you deep inside  I do not feel that I am my depression  nor do I identify with it  if anything I acknowledge it s there so that I can keep myself from sinking too deep when the next wave comes   That s why depression is such a huge problem  because it is often thought of something that easily brushes by you  But the reality of it is that it s debilitating  it can make it seem like even the simplest tasks are too much work  It s not something that s just over and done with it leaves a lot of damage behind in each wave  All I m going to say now it to try to avoid telling people with depression that it s not as bad as they think  and if you really want to help them offer a listening ear and let them know that there are people that care for them   That was just a quick rant
summary: Today my teacher played a video titled YOU ARE NOT DEPRESSED STOP IT on the topic of depression and suicide. As someone who has been diagnosed with clinical depression for years and has to take medication for it, he feels the video could have been better.
